# Engine vs content

This repo is **vtt-core** (tactical VTT engine). Hellpiercers IP lives in private git package `@vtt-core/hellpiercers-content` (`acedrow/hellpiercers-content`), installed to `node_modules`, registered at product boot.

## Dependency matrix

| Package | May depend on `@vtt-core/hellpiercers-content`? |
|---------|-----------------------------------------------|
| `@vtt-core/shared` | **No** |
| `@vtt-core/client` / `@vtt-core/server` / `@vtt-core/cf-worker` | **Yes** (product boots) |

Shared must not import the content package. Product packages side-effect-register at boot. Shared/client Vitest use fixture pack; HP suites live in `@vtt-core/hellpiercers-content` (see `docs/adr/006-testing-strategy.md`).

## Decisions (locked)

- Content = private git dep (`#semver:^0.0.8`). **Sync register-once** at boot (not runtime KV packs).
- Product boots: `@vtt-core/hellpiercers-content/register` (+ client `./register-client`). Never `@vtt-core/shared/register-hellpiercers`.
- Named combat implementations live in the content package and register via `CombatHookContribution.modules` + hooks; shared dispatches with `combatMod(key)`. Client board/combat UI helpers register via `ClientContribution.combatBoard.helpers` (not direct `./combat-ui` imports in engine source).
- Engine CI / shared Vitest target: fixture catalogs; content repo owns HP tests. Product/e2e registers Hellpiercers.
- npm package scope is `@vtt-core/*`.
- Nested `GameState.campaign` (parent #2) is done. Sheet/pack-version KV stamps + migrators (parent #7) are done in engine; content must ship `sheetDataKeys` (`@vtt-core/hellpiercers-content` ≥0.0.8).
- Client content exports include `./combat-ui` (content-internal / optional product), `./combat-board-placement`, `./tiles`, `./register`, `./register-client`. Residual peel: combat UI is contribution-hosted; see residual peel plans.
- ADRs: `docs/adr/001`–`008` (incl. package rename)
